subSubSection.paragraph:
Male genitalia:
Tergum IX and sternum IX distinctly separated from each other (
Fig. 5a
). Apical sclerites discernible in dorsal view (a.s. in 
Fig. 5d
), each with lower margin produced into triangular lobe at midlength. Preanal appendages subrectangular in lateral view (pre.app. in 
Fig. 5a
), slightly clavate in dorsal view (pre.app. in 
Fig. 5d
), with thickened bases and apices. Coxopodites fused and indistinguishable from basal plate (b.p. in 
Fig. 5e
). Harpagones setose, bifid, in ventral view pincer-shaped (har. in 
Fig. 5e
), each with lateral branch wider than mesal one. Phallic apparatus with phallotheca elliptical; endotheca with base having pair of processes (
Figs 5b, 5c, 5e
), and apex having apical hook in lateral view (
Fig. 5a
), and with ejaculatory duct opening anterior to apical hook.
